{"article_id":"01BNaWwS2avFtSOs","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Robert Mueller 's Russia Report Is Coming Thursday .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Here 's What You Need To Know","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"The Justice Department says","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"it plans to release special counsel Robert Mueller 's report on Thursday morning .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Here 's what you need to know .","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"Mueller was appointed in the spring of 2017","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"to investigate","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"whether President Trump 's campaign conspired with the Russian interference in the 2016 election .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"The fact of the interference itself had been long established ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"and last month Attorney General William Barr told Congress","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"that Mueller did not find","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"that Trump 's campaign was involved with it .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"Barr also told Congress","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that Mueller did n't establish","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"that Trump broke the law","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"in trying to frustrate the investigation","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"- but neither did Mueller 's office `` exonerate '' the president .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"Barr and Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein concluded for themselves ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"based on the special counsel 's findings ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"that Trump would not face obstruction-of-justice charges .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"What the document is expected to reveal are the factual findings and legal analysis","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"that underpinned the conclusions","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"already shared by Barr .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"Trump and Republicans have welcomed Barr 's summary ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"which","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"they say","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"vindicates the president","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"and gave them a surge of momentum into the burgeoning 2020 election season .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Democrats say","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"they ca n't be sure","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"Barr is n't providing political cover for Trump ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"pointing to skepticism","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"he voiced about Mueller 's inquiry","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"before he was nominated to be attorney general .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"Trump 's opponents say","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"they ca n't be sure what to make of Mueller 's findings","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"until they see the findings firsthand .","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"Nearly 400 pages , `` exclusive of tables and appendices , ''","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Barr told Congress .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"No .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"Barr told members of Congress","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"that he has been working with the special counsel 's office","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"to redact four kinds of information .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"First , grand jury material ,","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"which is secret under the law .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"Second , foreign intelligence","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that could compromise the sources and methods","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"from which it originated ,","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"which American spies want to protect .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"Third ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Barr said","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"he would redact information about ongoing cases or investigations","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"- those","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"taking place elsewhere in the Justice Department","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"now that the special counsel 's work is complete .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"Charges unsealed last week against Julian Assange , the founder of WikiLeaks ,","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"and Greg Craig , a former White House counsel , made clear","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"that legal aftershocks will continue","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"even though the big political quake in Washington apparently has passed .","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"And fourth ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"Barr told Congress ,","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"is `` information","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"that implicates the privacy or reputational interests of peripheral third parties","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"who were not charged . '' The Justice Department should not reveal derogatory information about people","depth":15},{"id":64,"text":"whom it is n't accusing of breaking the law ,","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"`` People in private life , ''","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"the attorney general told senators .","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"`` Not public officeholders . '' Could Barr try to protect political allies of the president ?","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"`` It seems to me that 's an exception","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"you can just drive a truck through , ''","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Rep. Ed Case , D-Hawaii , told Barr last week .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Trump 's opponents accuse Barr of working not as an independent arbiter but as a servant of the president .","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"Democrats were furious , for example ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"when Barr called the surveillance","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"conducted of Trump 's campaign in 2016","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"`` spying ''","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"- after the Russian government had launched its disinformation war on the presidential campaign .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi , D-Calif. , complained","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"that Barr was `` going off the rails ''","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"and that she did n't trust him .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"She 'll trust only what she reads from Mueller .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"The FBI and Justice Department conducted surveillance of Trump 's campaign in 2016","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"as they investigated the election interference .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"What Republicans have charged since is that some officials may have abused their powers","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"and violated the rights of at least one American .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Law enforcement officials have denied that","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"and defended their practices .","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"Barr and key Republicans in the Senate ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"including the chairman of the Senate Judiciary Committee , Sen. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. ,","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"say","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"they want answers to questions","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"about how and why decisions were made in 2016 .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"Barr told members of Congress","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"that another report is coming out this summer , after the Mueller report ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"that could provide some answers about that question .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"And Barr has launched his own informal review about the origins of the Russia investigation ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"meaning that this saga may continue to be not only about what Trump and his camp did","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"but about what investigators and Justice Department officials did too .","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"Why , for example , did n't officials brief Trump 's campaign in 2016 about the contacts","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"they were discovering","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"between people in his camp and Russians ?","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"How did the FBI use confidential informants","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"in trying to discover what Trump 's campaign was doing ?","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"One topic","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"it might explore","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"is what Trump and his top lieutenants in 2016 knew and when .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"Barr said","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"that Mueller did n't establish","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"that Trump 's campaign conspired with the Russians .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"But did Trump himself ever get word about the offers of help","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"that were coming in from Russians or their agents ,","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"including those to his son Donald Trump Jr. ?","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"If so ,","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"did Trump believe them","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"and actively decide not to accept what was being offered","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"- or did Trump just ignore them altogether ?","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"Americans have learned a lot from Mueller 's office about the methods","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"by which Russia interfered in the election .","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"The best-known schemes include agitation on social media","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"aimed at amplifying disagreements among Americans","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"and the cyberattacks","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"that stole data","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"that was then released","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"to embarrass political targets .","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"Others schemes","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"that have n't received as much attention","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"have been established too .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"Will Mueller 's report uncover any other types of interference","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"that have n't yet been made public ?","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"Barr and Rosenstein said","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"they 've concluded","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"that Trump wo n't face obstruction-of-justice charges .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"What did investigators uncover about what actions he took ?","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"How close was the call for the leaders of the Justice Department ?","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"Where did Mueller come down on all this ?","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"What recommendations did he make","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"- if any -","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"about charges for Trump ?","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"Did he defer that to the leaders of the Justice Department ,","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"or did he intend for conclusions about his findings and analysis to be reached by members of Congress ?","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"Barr says to expect some insights about all this :","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"The report `` sets forth the special counsel 's findings , his analysis and the reasons for his conclusions , ''","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"the attorney general wrote to Congress .","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"Barr 's letters about the work of the special counsel investigation have taken the wind from the sails of Democrats","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"who had been pushing for impeachment proceedings against Trump .","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"Members of Congress could resume that battle , however ,","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"if Mueller 's raw findings lead Trump 's opponents to conclude","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"he acted wrongly or abused his office , separate from Mueller 's or Barr 's reading of relevant criminal law .","depth":15},{"id":149,"text":"All these questions , legal wrangling , redactions - will this report make sense ?","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"`` Are we going to get the gist of this ,","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"or is it going to be ,","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"you know ,","depth":16},{"id":153,"text":"[ reading a section ] on January 2015","depth":16},{"id":154,"text":"and then you have to flip 15 pages","depth":16},{"id":155,"text":"to find the next text ? ''","depth":16},{"id":156,"text":"Schatz asked .","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"Barr said","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"the Justice Department would do better than that .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"par